name: window frame production, poly vinyl chloride, U=1.6 W/m2K | window frame, poly vinyl chloride, U=1.6 W/m2K | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/9378/documentation

This dataset describes all the processes and material inputs needed to produce a plastic window frame with 1 m2 visible area. 1 m2 of visible plastic window frame weighs 94.5 kg.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



Included processes are injection moulding and extrusion of PVC, section bar rolling for steel fittings, section bar extrusion for aluminium parts, all the road transport at different production phases and the process heat waste.
category: C:Manufacturing/22:Manufacture of rubber and plastics products/222:Manufacture of plastics products/2220:Manufacture of plastics products

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Window frames produced and sold in Switzerland and Germany.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The dataset describes highly automated technology processes in window frame manufacturing.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: see Geography This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography RER. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
